### Theme Presets
The system includes 8 predefined theme presets:
1. **Default** - Blue, Green, Orange
2. **Professional** - Navy, Teal, Gold
3. **Modern** - Purple, Pink, Blue
4. **Minimal** - Slate, Gray, Black
5. **Vibrant** - Orange, Purple, Pink
6. **Nature** - Green, Brown, Amber
7. **Ocean** - Blue, Cyan, Teal
8. **Sunset** - Orange, Red, Pink

## ðŸŒ™ Dark Mode Implementation

Dark mode is managed by [src/composables/useTheme.js](mdc:src/composables/useTheme.js) and toggled via [src/components/ThemeSwitcher.vue](mdc:src/components/ThemeSwitcher.vue).

### Dark Mode Composable
```javascript
import { useTheme } from '@/composables/useTheme'

const { isDarkMode, toggleDarkMode, setTheme } = useTheme()

// Toggle dark mode
toggleDarkMode()

// Set specific theme
setTheme('professional')

// Check current mode
console.log(isDarkMode.value) // true/false
```

### Dark Mode Classes
Always include dark mode variants in components:

```vue
<!-- Backgrounds -->
<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800">

<!-- Text -->
<p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">

<!-- Borders -->
<div class="border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">

<!-- Status badges -->
<span class="bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900/30 text-green-800 dark:text-green-200">
```

